To write a script that denies access to a website or service, you can use various methods depending on the technology and platform you are working with. Below is a simple example using JavaScript that can be implemented on a web server to block access to a specific webpage. 

This script will display a "Access Denied" page when a user tries to access the restricted content.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Access Denied</title>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Access Denied</h1>
    <p>You do not have permission to view this content.</p>
    <script>
        // Function to handle the blocking process
        function blockAccess() {
            var user = prompt("Please enter your username and password to access this content.");
            if (user == "") {
                window.location.href = "denied.html";
            } else {
                // Validate the user credentials here
                var correctUser = "exampleUser";
                if (user == correctUser) {
                    window.location.href = "allowed.html";
                } else {
                    alert("Access denied. Please try again.");
                }
            }
        }

        // Check if the user is already logged in
        if (!sessionStorage.getItem("userLoggedIn")) {
            blockAccess();
        }
    </script>
</body>
</html>
```

In this script, when a user tries to access the restricted content, they will be prompted to enter their username and password. If the entered credentials are correct, they will be redirected to the "allowed.html" page. Otherwise, they will see an "Access Denied" page. 

